7 A Concurrent Resolution declaring May 14, 2025, as
the 9th annual Hispanic Cultural Day in Oklahoma;
8 recognizing the Hispanic community in Oklahoma; and
celebrating the heritage, culture, and contributions
9 of Hispanics to the State of Oklahoma.
10
11 WHEREAS, Hispanics are those who identify their origin as the
12 heritage, nationality group, lineage, or country of their birth or
13 that of their parents or ancestors before their arrival into the
14 United States; and
15 WHEREAS, Spanish-speaking countries include Argentina, Bolivia,
16 Chile, Colombia, Costa Rica, Cuba, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, El
17 Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, México, Nicaragua, Panamá, Paraguay,
18 Perú, Spain, Uruguay, Venezuela, and the Commonwealth of Puerto
19 Rico; and
20 WHEREAS, Hispanics have been a part of the geography and history
21 of Oklahoma since the 16th Century when the Spanish initially
22 claimed Oklahoma, specifically the Oklahoma Panhandle; and
23 WHEREAS, the first exploration of Oklahoma was led by the
24 Spaniard Francisco Vásquez de Coronado and his army in 1541 on their
