1 jour ney to conquer the Seven Cities of Cíbola or Quivira, the area
2 known today as Cimarron County; and
3 WHEREAS, the majority of Oklahoma's Hispanic population live in
4 the cities of Oklahoma City, Tulsa, and Guymon; and
5 WHEREAS, Hispanics have migrated to the State of Oklahoma hoping
6 for better lives than the ones they left behind; and
7 WHEREAS, the influence of Hispanics in Oklahoma is a result of
8 their perseverance through hard times as well as their innate
9 yearning to establish a sense of place; and
10 WHEREAS, the median age of non-Hispanics in the United States is
11 fifty-four (54) years of age, the Hispanic median age is thirty (30)
12 years of age; and
13 WHEREAS, the economic impact of the Hispanic population in the
14 United States would rank as the fifth-largest economy in the world.
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
16 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
17 CONCURRING THEREIN:
18 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the Oklahoma
19 State Senate declare May 14, 2025, as the 9th annual Hispanic
20 Cultural Day in Oklahoma.
21 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives and Oklahoma State
22 Senate do hereby recognize the heritage, culture, and immense
23 contributions of Hispanics to the State of Oklahoma.
